Contractor safety procedures are reviewed to ensure outside workers exercise the same safety consciousness as employees;

A work permit system that ensures all welding work is conducted safely;

Process safety information; and

Emergency planning and response.



The brewery additionally complies with the requirements of the OSHA PSM standard (40 CFR 1910.119), the EPA RMP rules (40 CFR 68), and applicable Recognized and Generally Accepted Refrigeration System Practices for Equipment, Design, and Installation of Ammonia Mechanical Refrigerating Systems.



Five-Year Accident History

The brewery has had no releases that have caused onsite or offsite injuries, or damage to property or the environment. 



Emergency Response Program

The Houston brewery has in place a variety of emergency response procedures in the event of an incident involving ammonia. The emergency response program is based on OSHA's requirements for emergency action plans (29 CFR 1910.38) and HAZWOPER (29 CFR 1910.120). We have trained employees for emergency response and maintain a plan titled ES Incident Plan (HAZWOPER Plan) which has been supplied to, and discussed with, Greater Houston LEPC. We conduct annual drills with local agencies to help
